This paper deals with OCR (Optical Character Recognition) which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper discusses lexicon-based OCR systems and their limitations, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes two explicit confidence measurement techniques, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
